  "commentary": "**DEALER HEDGING COMMENTARY:**\n\nDealers are caught in a massive negative gamma trap with SPX sitting right at the -38.2B max negative gamma strike of 6590, forcing them to buy this rally and amplify upward momentum in classic breakout regime fashion. The cluster of heavy negative gamma walls from 6575-6590 creates a dangerous feedback loop where any upward price action will trigger aggressive dealer buying, while the lone positive gamma wall at 6605 (+22.0B) represents the first meaningful resistance where dealers will begin selling into strength. Watch 6605 as the critical flip point - a break above triggers more dealer buying toward higher strikes, while rejection here could send price cascading back through the negative gamma minefield below.\n\n**Bottom line:** expect explosive moves higher until 6605, then potential sharp reversal.",
